The Google Events Results API allows advanced filtering to get the results you specifically filter.
For example, the parameters above provide only today's online events.

GET


https://serpapi.com/search.json?engine=google_events&q=Events+in+Chicago&hl=en&gl=us&htichips=event_type:Virtual-Event,date:today

Code to integrate


Ruby

require "serpapi" 

client = SerpApi::Client.new(
  engine: "google_events",
  q: "Events in Chicago",
  hl: "en",
  gl: "us",
  htichips: "event_type:Virtual-Event,date:today",
  api_key: "697c05cd6b6463eba244ca9769758ae5a3d4bc0e6547fc72797084d3d01665d9"
)

results = client.search
events_results = results[:events_results]

